Jimmy Carter to observe Nicaragua election . Former U . S . President Jimmy Carter will be an observer at Nicaragua ' s Oct . 20 elections , a Carter Centre official said on Thursday . Carter will arrive in Nicaragua on Oct . 18 for a five - day visit accompanied by former U . S . Secretary of State James Baker , the head of the Carter Centre observer mission in Nicaragua , Jennifer McCoy , said . " He ' s coming to observe the elections and promote a peaceful transfer of power in Nicaragua , " McCoy said . The elections will mark the first transfer of power from one elected , civilian government to another in Nicaragua . 
